<div style="font-size:90%">
<br><br>

<b>First-ever Inter-federation practice and enbukai to raise funds for Iwama Dojo</b><br><br><br>
(Click <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=88TjlNPEoQ4" target=_blank>here</a> to view the video of the enbukai portion of this now-concluded event.)<br><br>

The Sendai earthquake of March 2011 sparks a first in the Filipino aikido community: an inter-federation practice and enbukai (demonstration). The proceeds of this event will all go to Hombu Dojo for its fund-raising campaign to rebuild the Iwama Dojo, heavily damaged by the March earthquake. Mat contribution is P200.<br><br>

The inter-federation training and demonstration will be held at the Club 650, along E. Rodriguez Avenue (C5), Libis, Quezon City, on Saturday, 2011 May 14th. The proceedings start at 18:30 hrs.<br><br>

This event is organized by Pilipinas Aikido Propagation Association (PAPA), the Filipino Federation of Aikido (FFA), and Aikido Philippines (AP).<br><br>

<br>


</div>

